---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SunCalculator from '../components/SunCalculator.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="Sun Calculator — Sunrise, Sunset & Daylight Hours | Clockr"
	description="Find sunrise, sunset and daylight hours for any location and date. See solar noon, dawn, dusk and a visual daylight timeline."
	category="seasons"
>
	<div class="sc-page">
		<div class="sc-header">
			<div class="sc-eyebrow">
				<span class="sc-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				SEASONS
			</div>
			<h1 class="sc-title">
				<span class="sc-gradient">Sun Calculator</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="sc-subtitle">
				Find sunrise, sunset and daylight hours for any location and date
			</p>
		</div>

		<SunCalculator client:load />

		<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
		<section class="sc-how">
			<h2 class="sc-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="sc-how-card">
				<p>
					Sunrise and sunset are not fixed clock times — they depend on where you
					are on Earth, the date, and how the planet is tilted on its axis. This
					calculator uses a standard solar-position algorithm (the same family of
					formulas used by NOAA and other astronomical references) with each
					city&apos;s latitude and longitude from our 250-city database. For any
					chosen date it works out when the Sun crosses the horizon, when it
					reaches its highest point (solar noon), and how many hours of daylight
					you get — all in local time for that city.
				</p>
				<p>
					Daylight length changes through the year because Earth&apos;s axis is
					tilted about 23.5° relative to its orbit. Near the summer solstice,
					the Northern Hemisphere leans toward the Sun, so days are longest;
					near the winter solstice they are shortest. The effect is strongest at
					high latitudes — Edinburgh sees dramatic swings between long June days
					and short December ones, while cities near the equator have roughly
					equal day and night year-round. Your distance from the equator
					(latitude) sets the range; the time of year sets where you are within
					that range.
				</p>
				<p>
					Twilight is the period when the Sun is below the horizon but the sky
					is still partly lit. <strong>Civil twilight</strong> (used for dawn and
					dusk here) ends when the Sun is 6° below the horizon — roughly when
					outdoor activities are still possible without artificial light.
					<strong>Nautical twilight</strong> (12° below) is when the horizon at
					sea is still visible; <strong>astronomical twilight</strong> (18° below)
					is when the faintest stars begin to appear. Dawn is civil twilight
					before sunrise; dusk is civil twilight after sunset.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- FAQ -->
		<section class="sc-faq">
			<h2 class="sc-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="sc-faq-list">
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question">What time is sunrise today?</summary>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Select your city and leave the date on today (or tap the
							&ldquo;Today&rdquo; quick link). The sunrise time appears in the
							results panel, shown in local time for that city. Times update
							automatically for the current date and shift slightly each day as
							Earth moves along its orbit.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question"
						>Why do sunrise and sunset times change throughout the year?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Earth&apos;s 23.5° axial tilt means different parts of the planet
							receive more or less sunlight as we orbit the Sun. In summer (around
							the June solstice in the Northern Hemisphere), days grow longer;
							in winter they shrink. The change is gradual through spring and
							autumn and fastest around the equinoxes, when day and night are
							nearly equal.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question">What is solar noon?</summary>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Solar noon is the moment when the Sun reaches its highest point in
							the sky for that day. It is not always exactly 12:00 on your clock
							— clock noon is a time-zone convention, while solar noon depends on
							your longitude and the equation of time (Earth&apos;s slightly
							elliptical orbit). It usually falls within an hour or so of midday
							local time.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question">What is civil twilight?</summary>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Civil twilight occurs when the Sun is between 0° and 6° below the
							horizon. There is enough natural light to see clearly outside, but
							street lights may switch on. Dawn (civil) begins at the end of
							night; dusk (civil) ends when the sky is dark enough for most stars
							to be visible. This calculator shows civil dawn and dusk times.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question"
						>Which place has the most daylight hours?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							On the summer solstice, high-latitude cities in the Northern
							Hemisphere — such as Reykjavik, Helsinki, or Anchorage — have the
							longest days, sometimes with nearly 24 hours of light (midnight sun
							above the Arctic Circle). Near the equator, daylight stays close to
							12 hours all year. Use the quick links to compare solstice dates
							for different cities.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question"
						>How are sunrise and sunset times calculated?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Clockr uses a standard solar-position model based on NOAA/USNO
							algorithms. Given a date, latitude, and longitude, it calculates
							the Sun&apos;s declination and hour angle, then finds when the
							solar disc crosses the horizon (accounting for atmospheric
							refraction). Results are converted to the city&apos;s IANA time
							zone, including daylight saving time where applicable. No external
							API is required.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- RELATED TOOLS -->
		<div class="sc-related">
			<h3 class="sc-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="sc-related-grid">
				<a href="/season-countdown" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Season Countdown</span></a
				>
				<a href="/moon-phase-calculator" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Moon Phase Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/year-progress" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Year Progress Bar</span></a
				>
				<a href="/timezone-converter" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Time Zone Converter</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
	.sc-page {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.sc-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.sc-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-eyebrow-square {
		width: 8px;
		height: 8px;
		border-radius: 2px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		flex-shrink: 0;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: initial;
	}

	.sc-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-gradient {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.sc-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.sc-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.sc-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.sc-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.sc-how-card strong {
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.sc-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.sc-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.sc-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.sc-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.sc-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-faq-item[open] .sc-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.sc-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.sc-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.sc-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.sc-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.sc-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.sc-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.4);
	}

	.sc-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.sc-title {
			font-size: 44px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		.sc-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}

	/* Sun Calculator tool */
	.sunc-tool {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.sunc-inputs {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 20px;
		margin-bottom: 20px;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.sunc-inputs {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}

	.sunc-label {
		display: block;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
		margin-bottom: 8px;
	}

	.sunc-location-wrap {
		position: relative;
	}

	.sunc-location-input {
		width: 100%;
		box-sizing: border-box;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.25);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 14px 16px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: #fff;
		outline: none;
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			box-shadow 0.2s ease;
	}

	.sunc-location-input:focus {
		border-color: rgba(116, 180, 155, 0.6);
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
	}

	.sunc-location-input::placeholder {
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
		font-weight: 500;
	}

	.sunc-picker-list {
		position: absolute;
		top: calc(100% + 6px);
		left: 0;
		right: 0;
		z-index: 20;
		max-height: 280px;
		overflow-y: auto;
		margin: 0;
		padding: 6px;
		list-style: none;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
	}

	.sunc-picker-item {
		display: block;
		width: 100%;
		padding: 10px 12px;
		background: none;
		border: none;
		border-radius: 8px;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75);
		text-align: left;
		cursor: pointer;
		transition: background 0.15s ease;
	}

	.sunc-picker-item:hover {
		background: rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
	}

	.sunc-picker-empty {
		padding: 12px;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
		text-align: center;
	}

	.sunc-date-wrap {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: flex-start;
	}

	.sunc-quick-dates {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 8px;
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	.sunc-quick-btn {
		padding: 8px 14px;
		background: rgba(12, 12, 12, 0.6);
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.25);
		border-radius: 999px;
		cursor: pointer;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			background 0.2s ease;
	}

	.sunc-quick-btn:hover {
		border-color: rgba(116, 180, 155, 0.5);
		background: rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.08);
	}

	.sunc-quick-btn--active {
		border-color: rgba(116, 180, 155, 0.7);
		background: rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		color: #fff;
	}

	.sunc-hero-band {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		width: 100vw;
		margin-left: calc(50% - 50vw);
		padding: 48px 24px 56px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d1f17, #1a2e24);
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.25);
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.25);
	}

	.sunc-hero-centre {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		text-align: center;
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 640px;
	}

	.sunc-result-location {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);
		margin: 0 0 6px;
	}

	.sunc-result-date {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		margin: 0 0 24px;
	}

	.sunc-daylight-hero {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(28px, 5vw, 40px);
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -1px;
		line-height: 1.1;
		margin: 0 0 28px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sunc-daylight-hero-label {
		font-size: 0.55em;
		font-weight: 600;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		background: none;
	}

	.sunc-daylight-bar-wrap {
		width: 100%;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.sunc-daylight-bar {
		position: relative;
		height: 14px;
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 999px;
		overflow: visible;
		margin-bottom: 8px;
	}

	.sunc-daylight-seg {
		position: absolute;
		top: 0;
		height: 100%;
		border-radius: 0;
	}

	.sunc-daylight-seg--night {
		background: #1a1a2e;
	}

	.sunc-daylight-seg--dawn,
	.sunc-daylight-seg--dusk {
		background: linear-gradient(90deg, #1a1a2e, #74b49b);
	}

	.sunc-daylight-seg--dusk {
		background: linear-gradient(90deg, #74b49b, #1a1a2e);
	}

	.sunc-daylight-seg--day {
		background: linear-gradient(90deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
	}

	.sunc-daylight-now {
		position: absolute;
		top: 50%;
		width: 4px;
		height: 22px;
		margin-left: -2px;
		margin-top: -11px;
		border-radius: 2px;
		background: #fff;
		box-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		z-index: 2;
	}

	.sunc-daylight-labels {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.35);
	}

	.sunc-polar-note {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0 0 24px;
	}

	.sunc-stats-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
		width: 100%;
	}

	@media (max-width: 560px) {
		.sunc-stats-grid {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		}
	}

	.sunc-stat {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 6px;
		padding: 16px 12px;
		background: rgba(12, 12, 12, 0.5);
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.2);
		border-radius: 12px;
	}

	.sunc-stat-value {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(16px, 3vw, 20px);
		font-weight: 800;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		text-align: center;
		line-height: 1.2;
	}

	.sunc-stat-label {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 1px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		text-align: center;
	}
</style>
